unrepresentative they may be of the world's Muslims, in a world the
way it is now, too many people are just itching to find some excuse to
declare a big chunk of the world - such as that on which the world's
one billion Muslims reside - officially vacant so that it can be
parcelled out to solve problems, like those of the Tamils in Sri
Lanka, the East Indians in Fiji, the Ibos in Nigeria, and so on and so
forth. So we can make amends to the Hopi and the Hawaiians by letting
them join in doing to the Muslims what we once did to their ancestors.

Between things like global warming on the one hand, and the bleak
prospect of a world chasing its own tail in a cycle of terror and
genocide, getting some people off the Earth seems to be a priority,
not an extremely far-sighted ambition. If we're *lucky*, instead of a
few dozen colonists establishing the Human Race Mark II, we might
survive long enough to be able to usefully receive help from their
descendants.

John Savard
